</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F5B3C96644D274AA867709611A33C97B" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="notes">
<paragraph id="B7C488C3C9FAAD4B4D4F12A388734F5A" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F5E3AC91BF259143210B3C0B9F85FF9B" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
The type locality of 
<taxonomicName id="21309F98CD2C6B961C02BFE8230A8C1D" authority="C.D.Specht" authorityName="Skornick." authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Leong-Škorničková &amp; Böhmová &amp; Tr ần" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Costaceae" genus="Cheilocostus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cheilocostus tonkinensis" order="Zingiberales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tonkinensis">
<emphasis id="2BFE9349271D609B786D059FA728F7F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Cheilocostus tonkinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in northern Vietnam, Mount Ba 
<normalizedToken id="142D19593544DA6AB36EB306DDFB359F" originalValue="Vì">Vi</normalizedToken>
. In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation id="3179666F643A466AF6E88D19707D8AAD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00378941.1902.10830936" author="Gagnepain, F" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" pagination="247 - 269" refId="B2" refString="Gagnepain, F, 1902. [publ. 1903] Zingiberacees Nouvelles de L'herbier du Museum (1). Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France 49 (5): 247 - 269, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00378941.1902.10830936" title="[publ. 1903] Zingiberacees Nouvelles de L'herbier du Museum (1)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00378941.1902.10830936" volume="49" year="1902">Gagnepain (1902)</bibRefCitation>
refers to two collections made by Balansa from this locality. There are four sheets at P: a single sheet of 
<emphasis id="FACC71E5A49EE6B2FEA1629ADC7BA767" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Balansa s.n.</emphasis>
, collected on 24 July 1886 [P00686610 - inflorescences &amp; flower] and three sheets of 
<emphasis id="1FE368C52165CC0C4793FC29221E870F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Balansa 4206</emphasis>
collected in October 1887 [P02198384 - leafy shoot &amp; single fruit; P02198381-inflorescence only; P02198385-leafy shoot only]. Both of these collections predate the protologue and are annotated in 
<normalizedToken id="21FA1CDFA5AA61E40C59EAE82ECAE948" originalValue="Gagnepain’s">Gagnepain's</normalizedToken>
hand as published in Bull. Bot Soc. France 49: 248. All four sheets have to be considered as syntypes and, therefore, the lectotypification is needed. Unfortunately, none of the specimens consists of both leafy shoot and an inflorescence. 
<emphasis id="3ABB9F6E1B77184E1DE2829E17B524EF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Balansa s.n.</emphasis>
[P00686610] with inflorescence and a flower, accompanied by a pencil drawing, is selected here as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99D3FC118351A59BBFE15E2230C689D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
It is challenging to distinguish Asian radically flowering 
<taxonomicName id="92818803180FD24EEB80915C924934B8" authority="C.D.Specht" authorityName="C.D.Specht" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Costaceae" genus="Cheilocostus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Zingiberales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Costaceae</taxonomicName>
in herbarium material as the flowers do not preserve well. Based on our observations of living flowering material and photographic records with location data, 
<taxonomicName id="2E277DB0B7C400618E16960C7BECF47D" authority="C.D.Specht" authorityName="Skornick." authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Leong-Škorničková &amp; Böhmová &amp; Tr ần" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Costaceae" genus="Cheilocostus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cheilocostus tonkinensis" order="Zingiberales" pageId="0" pageNumber="103" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tonkinensis">
<emphasis id="1EFC62C105F356C05BFBDB0D798EF033" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Cheilocostus tonkinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so far, occurs in S. China, northern and central Vietnam and northern Laos, but may possibly extend to Thailand.
</paragraph>
